> Pasta + pesto + Parmesan cheese: it's an equation that never fails. Add in a
> crispy panko breadcrumb topping and now things are really starting to add up.
> But to really make this dish worth more than the sum of its parts, you gotta
> add in a powerhouse veggie like kale. It takes this tortelloni bake from
> creamy and crusty to hale and hearty and incredibly satisfying.

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler to high or #oven{} to 500 degrees.
Thinly slice @garlic{4%cloves}. Remove and discard stems and large ribs from
@kale{8%ounce}. Thinly slice leaves.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{5%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium heat.
Add garlic and toss until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Add kale and a splash
of @water{}. Cook, tossing, until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

Add @milk{2%cup}, @organic veggie stock{2}, and @pesto{4%ounce} to pan and stir
to combine. Add @cheese tortelloni{18%ounce} to pan in a single layer.

Bring pesto sauce to a boil, then reduce heat. Simmer, stirring occasionally,
until sauce is thick and tortelloni are tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> TIP: If your pan is not ovenproof, transfer everything to a baking dish after
> simmering.

While tortelloni simmer, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @Parmesan cheese{1/2%cup},
and @olive oil{1%TBSP} in a #small bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper. Once
tortelloni are done simmering, sprinkle panko mixture over pan or #baking dish{}.

Transfer tortelloni to broiler or oven. Broil or bake until browned and bubbly,
~{1-2%minutes}. Divide tortelloni between bowls and serve.